{"id": 12, "ts": 1778868646.2233286, "event": "public_discussion_message", "round": 1, "agent": "agent_1", "message": "I\u2019ve compiled what we each know about the four candidates and identified the remaining gaps that are most relevant to a long\u2011distance pilot role.\n**Candidate A**\n- Strengths: anticipates dangerous situations, sees complex connections, excellent spatial vision, very good leadership qualities.\n- Weaknesses: sometimes not good at taking criticism, can be unorganized.\n- **Missing info:** explicit statements about reliability/responsibility and technical competence (beyond situational awareness).\n**Candidate B**\n- Strengths: keeps calm in a crisis, 100\u202f% reliable, good at assessing weather conditions, excellent computer skills.\n- Weaknesses: can be grumpy, uncooperative, makes nasty remarks about colleagues.\n- **Missing info:** any further evidence of teamwork/crew\u2011cooperation beyond the positives already listed.\n**Candidate C**\n- Strengths: makes correct decisions quickly, handles stress very well, creates a positive atmosphere with his crew.\n- Weaknesses: difficulty communicating ideas, regarded as egocentric, not very willing to further his education.\n- **Missing info:** explicit technical competence and reliability.\n**Candidate D**\n- Strengths: responds to unexpected events adequately, concentrates very well, solves problems extremely well, takes responsibility seriously.\n- Weaknesses: regarded as arrogant, relatively weak leadership skills, has a hot temper.\n- **Missing info:** explicit technical competence, reliability, and concrete leadership strengths (beyond responsibility).\n**Key uncertainties that could shift the assessment**\n1. **Reliability of A and D** \u2013 we have no direct statements.\n2. **Technical competence of A, C, and D** \u2013 only indirect hints.\n3. **Leadership strength of D** \u2013 we know leadership is weak, but any specific positive aspects?\n4. **Teamwork/crew cooperation of C** \u20